dataIdInfo.idPurp: This python toolbox is a series of tools designed to enable common compliance workflows in ArcGIS Pro for financial services organizations.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
There are 3 primary workflows encapsulated within this toolbox

  • Build FFIEC Feature Class - Takes raw FFIEC data and a census tract layer as input to construct a foundational census tract geography layer containing FFIEC variables. This layer can be used for visualization or to support other downstream analyses.

  • Enrich Customer Portfolio with FFIEC Data - Takes an input layer representing customer points and enriches those customer points with attributes from an FFIEC Feature Class. This allows the analyst to associate FFIEC variables to each individual customer for the purpose of visualization and reporting.

  • BISG (Surgeo 1.1.2) - Takes a customer layer containing Census Tract FIPS codes and surnames to generate probabilities of race/ethnicity for each customer point. This tool leverages the Surgeo python library as the BISG engine.
